productInformation.name: Care instructions
productInformation.value: ‎Daily Care Instructions: Sterilize each pacifier before use by pouring boiling water over it in a clean bowl, letting dry on a clean towel and squeeze any remaining water out from the nipple. Make sure the pacifier is completely cooled down before giving it to the baby. We recommend replacing the pacifiers every 4 to 6 weeks for hygienic reasons.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: We've used BIBS since my daughter was born and now that she's 18 months we are happy to move up to this size. Yes it's larger, but so important for the growth and development of the mouth to have that larger size. I'm super aware and cautious with when it's used and how it's used. As a preschool teacher I really don't want her having it all the time , specially when trying to talk or learn to talk. It's one reason I like the larger size. It's for safe self soothing during times when sleeping or needing comfort. Granted we all have different opinions and parenting philosophies, I'm very pleased and feel it's very safe and great quality.

Nous avons utilisé ces tétines pour ma fille durant 3 ans car ce sont les seules qu'elle a accepté bébé.Nous avons tout d'abord été séduit par l'esthétique de ces tétines, le choix des couleurs formes ect...Mais nous avons été déçus par deux points importants.Le premier ; l'hygiène. Toute les petites poussières s'accumulent au niveau de la séparation entre le plastique et l'embout (sf photo) et pas facile à nettoyerLe deuxième et le plus dommageable pour nous : les dents de notre fille ont poussées et la dentition a prit la forme arrondie de la tétine car nous n'avons jamais réussi à trouver une autre marque qui lui convenait et elle vient tout juste d'arrêter de s'en servir.Je ne recommande pas aux jeunes parents cet achat et nous n'avons jamais proposé ces tétines à notre nouveau né par craintes pour ces dents

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. We’ve used the bibs deluxe dummies almost exclusively since my daughter was born. She loves the round latex dummy teats - I guess you don’t always have a choice over which one they like, but these were the best we were able to find.Unfortunately they aren’t made for the 18 month+ category, so we moved over to the standard Bibs dummies. Beyond the marginally cheaper price, I have not been such a huge fan, and neither has my daughter.Most notably, the teat size is a huge step up from the size below. Ridiculously so. My daughter hated them. In fact she’s rejected them entirely. Even now at age two she won’t take them and still just calls them ‘fat dodie’ and throws them away. I’ve included a picture comparing them to the Bibs deluxe size two dummies.The colours are still lovely, but I do like the design less than the deluxe dummies. The ring moves around too easily and makes an audible rattle - far too distracting to play with for a little one that needs to sleep. I also don’t love the look of the teat forming a ring above the plastic circle. The design reminds me of the Frigg dummies, though a little less nice.We obviously haven’t really tested the functionality of these dummies over the long-term, but if they’re anything like other Bibs dummies they will be hardy, easy to clean and will avoid indentations on your child’s face due to their design.Such a shame about the size. I could have lived with everything else.
